  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The event mechanism"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "is a means of synchronisation",
        "is only provided for extended tasks",
        "initiates state transitions of tasks to and from the waiting state"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "panel_type": "info",
      "title": "",
      "content": "Any task or ISR of category 2 can set an event for a not suspended extended task, and thus inform the extended task about any status change via this event"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Synchronization of preemptable extended tasks"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Task T1 waits for an event. Task T2 sets this event for T1. The scheduler is activated. Subsequently, T1 is transferred from the waiting state into the ready state. Due to the higher priority of T1 this results in a task switch, T2 being preempted by T1. T1 resets the event."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/5.%20Autosar%20-%20OS%20Event/image-2023-5-6_17-11-7.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/5. Autosar - OS Event/image-2023-5-6_17-11-7.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Synchronization of non-preemptable extended tasks"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If non preemptive scheduling is supposed, rescheduling does not take place immediately after the event has been set"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/5.%20Autosar%20-%20OS%20Event/image-2023-5-6_17-12-54.png?api=v2",
